  <static seed="732">
    <statement><p>Find the vertex coordinates for the function with formula <m>f(x)=\frac12x^2+8x+2\text{.}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="16" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(-8,-30\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Since <m>h=-\frac{b}{2a}\text{,}</m> we have <m>h=-\frac{8}{2(1/2)}=-8\text{.}</m> And then</p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
k \amp=f(-8)\\
k \amp=\frac12(-8)^2+8(-8)+2\\
k \amp=\frac12(64)-64+2\\
k \amp=32-64+2\\
k \amp=-30
\end{aligned}</me></p>
<p>So the vertex is at <m>(-8,-30)\text{.}</m></p>
</solution>
